      "writtenOn": "2026-07-24T03:40:08Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "That is one of the main concerns I am having right now.\n\nThe idea was to implement another health property fetching path(through association with the state object), and then add it after the legacy path.\n\nWhenever a legacy path found the inventory item didn\u0027t have the `operationalStatus` dbus interface implemented, it then switches to the second path and look for any associated object implemented with this interface.",
      "parentUuid": "f36bf769_4c8e4bb6",
      "revId": "087d3d9ca4735325d0753902c73a9f09fd079614",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
    {
