      "writtenOn": "2026-07-24T03:40:08Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "That was a tricky part.\nI was trying to enable PLDM state sensor feature.\n\nOne of the state the state sensor exposes is the health state, which indicate the health state of the object it is currently monitoring.\n\nHowever, the state sensor is allowed to be turned off and the previous design in the following link used this `operationalStatus` interface and its property to represent whether the sensor has been turned on.\nhttps://github.com/openbmc/docs/blob/cf706722293b681fbcbb852eee05a9ae045ac635/designs/pldm-stack.md?plain\u003d1#L514\n\nThis act makes the sensor unable to publishes the health state of the monitoring object, using the same PDI. Also, the current PDI of `operationalStatus` has no association to link the state object with the monitoring inventory item such as processor, PCIeDevice, etc.",
      "parentUuid": "aefdd42c_f721c777",
      "revId": "087d3d9ca4735325d0753902c73a9f09fd079614",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    }
